2026 Regular Session ENROLLED
SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 167
BY SENATOR BARROW
A RESOLUTION
To recognize Friday, May 29, 2026, as Youth Legislature of Louisiana Day at the Louisiana
State Capitol and to commend Youth Legislature of Louisiana for its longstanding
commitment to civic education, leadership development, and student engagement in
the legislative process and to recognize its transformative impact on young leaders
throughout the state of Louisiana.
WHEREAS, Youth Legislature of Louisiana is an educational program dedicated to
inspiring and empowering future generations of leaders through civic engagement and
experiential learning; and
WHEREAS, founded in 1978, Youth Legislature of Louisiana has been shaped by
decades of passionate students, educators, mentors, and civic leaders, providing an
opportunity for young people to foster and develop skills to experience the responsibilities
of lawmakers, engage in critical analysis of public policy, and influence meaningful change
for the betterment of the state; and
WHEREAS, the program has established itself as an innovative and highly respected
model for civic education, cultivating informed, engaged, and confident young citizens
equipped to participate actively in the democratic process; and
WHEREAS, each year, more than one thousand eight hundred middle school
students representing diverse educational settings across approximately fifteen parishes
participate in mock legislative sessions held at the historic Old State Capitol in Baton Rouge
serving as legislators, committee chairs, members of the media, and executive branch
officials, thereby gaining firsthand knowledge of the legislative process and the
responsibilities of public service; and
WHEREAS, by simulating the legislative process, the program deepens civic
engagement and understanding, enabling students to learn how laws are created and
demonstrating the profound impact their voices can have within their communities and
across the state; and
