WHEREAS, Youth Legislature of Louisiana further strengthens critical thinking by
encouraging participants to analyze real-world issues, evaluate competing viewpoints, and
develop persuasive, solution-oriented proposals; and
WHEREAS, students participating in the program develop confidence and
proficiency in public speaking as they learn to present ideas effectively, advocate for
legislation, and communicate with clarity and conviction; and
WHEREAS, through hands-on education and meaningful collaboration, students not
only gain a greater appreciation for government and public service but also build lasting
relationships, strengthen their sense of civic responsibility, and discover their own potential
to shape the future of Louisiana.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
does hereby recognize Friday, May 29, 2026, as Youth Legislature of Louisiana Day at the
Louisiana State Capitol, does hereby commend Youth Legislature of Louisiana for its
extraordinary contributions to civic education and youth leadership development, and does
hereby recognize its enduring impact in preparing future generations of engaged and
informed citizens.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to
Cheryle Totten, Founder and Executive Director of the Youth Legislature of Louisiana.
PRESIDENT OF THE SENATE
